{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3131804,"name":"java4first","username":"java4first","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/6bbea6/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-01-22T12:08:55.504Z","cooked":"<p>I am trying to persist a team / robot specific table following the examples and the API docs.  It seems like the following code should work, and generate a networktables.json that is there the next time the robot code restarts / runs. But I never get a file generated:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">      NetworkTableInstance inst = NetworkTableInstance.getDefault();
      NetworkTable table = inst.getTable("501Prefs");

      StringTopic configTopic = table.getStringTopic("config");
      configTopic.setPersistent(true);
      configTopic.setRetained(true);

      configPub = configTopic.publish();
      configPub.set(VersionInfo.version);
      configPub.close();
</code></pre>
<p>Using Shuffleboard, I see my table while running, and it has the value for the entry. But there is no file generated, and restarting the code (without deploying new code) doesn’t create a file.</p>
<p>Also - I think there is a bug - as setting “Retained” is supposed to make the topic stay even if there are no publishers (at least according to the API docs) but if I don’t comment out the “configPub.close()” it goes away as soon as the publisher closes.</p>
<p>Anyway - does anyone have code that creates a table with one or more entries that persist (so I can manually edit the file on the filesystem and have it read in the values to populate my custom table when the code starts - that is the use case I am trying to get back to with this new version).</p>
<p>Thanks!<br>
Stu</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2023-01-22T12:08:55.504Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":76,"reads":111,"readers_count":110,"score":402.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":424325,"topic_slug":"how-to-persist-networktables-nt4","display_username":"java4first","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":14762,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/how-to-persist-networktables-nt4/424325/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3131843,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-22T15:42:47.790Z","cooked":"<p>The problem is you’re setting properties on the topic before publishing it.  As there are no publishers, the topic doesn’t actually exist yet, so there’s nothing to set the properties on.  This is an area where the API shape doesn’t match the underlying behavior.</p>
<p>I think you’re right that this is something that we probably want to have work, as it’s confusing that it doesn’t, so I’ll look into a way to make this work (or at least give a warning if we can’t make it work).</p>
